  ${
    $d x y $.
    $( Axiom of Distinct Variables.  The only axiom of predicate calculus
       requiring that variables be distinct (if we consider ~ ax-17 to be a
       metatheorem and not an axiom).  Axiom scheme C16' in [Megill] p. 448 (p.
